# Configurazione MongoDB Atlas - Variabili d'Ambiente

## Development (.env.development)

```bash
# MongoDB Atlas Connection
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://qr-menu-dev@cluster0.XXXXX.mongodb.net/?authSource=$external&authMechanism=MONGODB-X509
MONGODB_CERT_PATH=C:/Users/gigli/Desktop/X509-cert-4084673564018728353.pem
MONGODB_DB_NAME=qr-menu-dev

# Migrazione da storage file (solo primo avvio!)
MIGRATE_FROM_FILES=true

# Server
PORT=8080
LOG_LEVEL=debug
```

## Production (.env.production)

```bash
# MongoDB Atlas Connection  
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://qr-menu-prod@cluster0.XXXXX.mongodb.net/?authSource=$external&authMechanism=MONGODB-X509
MONGODB_CERT_PATH=/etc/qr-menu/certs/X509-cert-XXXX.pem
MONGODB_DB_NAME=qr-menu

# NO migrazione in produzione!
MIGRATE_FROM_FILES=false

# Server
PORT=8080
LOG_LEVEL=info
```

## Come Usare

### Windows PowerShell

```powershell
# Carica le variabili (una tantum per sessione)
$env:MONGODB_URI="..."
$env:MONGODB_CERT_PATH="C:/Users/gigli/Desktop/X509-cert-4084673564018728353.pem"
$env:MONGODB_DB_NAME="qr-menu"
$env:MIGRATE_FROM_FILES="true"

# Esegui applicazione
go run main.go
```

### Linux/macOS

```bash
# Carica da file
source .env.development

# O esporta una tantum
export MONGODB_URI="..."
export MONGODB_CERT_PATH="./certs/X509-cert.pem"
export MONGODB_DB_NAME="qr-menu"
export MIGRATE_FROM_FILES="true"

# Esegui
go run main.go
```

### Docker

```dockerfile
FROM golang:1.24

# ... setup ...

# Copia certificato
COPY ./certs/X509-cert.pem /etc/qr-menu/certs/

# Environment variables
ENV MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://qr-menu-prod@cluster0.XXXXX.mongodb.net/?authSource=$external&authMechanism=MONGODB-X509
ENV MONGODB_CERT_PATH=/etc/qr-menu/certs/X509-cert.pem
ENV MONGODB_DB_NAME=qr-menu
ENV MIGRATE_FROM_FILES=false

CMD ["./qr-menu"]
```

## Note Importanti

⚠️ **SICUREZZA:**
- ❌ Non commitare il certificato X.509 in Git
- ❌ Non commitare .env file con secrets
- ✅ Usa `.env.example` per template
- ✅ Metti certificato in directory protetta
- ✅ Usa environment variables per produzione

📌 **MIGRAZIONE:**
- `MIGRATE_FROM_FILES=true` solo al primo avvio
- Dopodichè impostare a `false` per evitare duplicati
- La migrazione è **idempotente** (safe da re-eseguire)
